-- Pakistan Suicide Blast Kills 8 Near Political Rally in Peshawar
-- B y   A u g u s t i n e   A n t h o n y   a n d   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 2013-04-16T17:01:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-16/pakistan-suicide-blast-kills-8-near-political-rally-in-peshawar.html
A bomb blast next to a political
rally for the  Awami National Party  in Pakistan’s northwestern
city of  Peshawar  today killed eight people and injured 40,
according to one of the party’s senior leaders, Mian Iftikhar
Hussain.  The blast was a suicide attack, according to the city’s
police chief, Liaquat Ali, whose comments to reporters at the
site were carried on the Geo television channel along with
Hussain’s. Pakistan is scheduled to hold parliamentary elections
May 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Augustine Anthony in Islamabad at 
 aanthony9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
